'STRING FIND' LOCATES STRINGS INMEMORY.JUST 'BRUN STRING FIND' ANDENTER THE MONITOR WITH 'CALL -151'.THEN ENTER THE RANGE OF MEMORY FORTHE SEARCH (E.G.; D000.FFFF);FOLLOWED BY <CTRL>-YAND <RETURN>. A QUESTION MARK (?)PROMPT APPEARS; AND YOU TYPE THEASCII CHARACTERS OF THE STRING FORWHICH TO SEARCH. THE EIGHTH BIT OFEACHCHARACTER IS IGNORED; SO THE ROUTINECANFIND CHARACTERS IN EITHERPOSITIVE OR NEGATIVE ASCII.